Heavy floods rocked parts of the province in recent weeks causing damage to property and claiming lives. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service says there s a 60% chance of showers and thundershowers forecast for Gauteng tomorrow.Heavy floods rocked parts of the province in recent weeks causing damage to property and claiming lives while a body of three-year-old Everlate Chauke from Alexandra is still missing.It s been more than week since she was swept away during the recent flash floods in the province.Forecaster Venetia Phakula said, We are expecting rain and so far we re giving it a 60% chance of showers and thundershowers. They are most likely to start in the afternoon and starting from Monday, we are also keeping the rain over Gauteng but more of a 30% and them we see rain coming back from Wednesday. 